"""
CPFR KPI Tracking Pipeline - V3 (Action-Driving + Time Semantics + Confidence)

Aligned to canonical datasets with STAR model:
- DIM_ITEM: Item catalog (1 row per client_item_nbr)
- DIM_STORE: Store catalog (1 row per store_id)
- F_STORE_ITEM_LY: Multi-week LY sell-out (store × item × week)
- F_STORE_ITEM_CURRENT: Current snapshot (store × item + inventory + LW sellout)
- F_STORE_SUBCATEGORY_SEASON: Seasonal store-subcategory demand (allocation proxy)
- F_ACTIVE_STORE_ITEM: Active store-item combinations (MANDATORY FILTER)

Gold Fact: F_STORE_ITEM_WEEK (store × item × week with KPIs, flags, confidence)

Major upgrades vs V2:
1) Action-driving dictionary layer (KPI/flag → owner/action/priority/templates) via kpi_action_map.json
2) Explicit time semantics:
   - sellout_units_ly_yoy = same-week LY comparator (used for YoY)
   - history_weeks/history_units/history_cv = multi-week LY evidence window (used for confidence + low_history)
3) KPI confidence signal: HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
"""

